-- PZ Cussons of Nigeria Says Annual Profit Advances 4.7% Even as Sales Drop
-- Ana Monteiro
-- 2010-07-30T10:15:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-30/pz-cussons-of-nigeria-says-annual-profit-advances-4-7-even-as-sales-drop.html

          
          
             PZ Cussons Plc, a Nigerian consumer-
goods maker, said profit for the year through December climbed
4.7 percent.  
 Net income advanced to 5.58 billion naira from 5.33 billion
naira a year earlier, the company said in a statement e-mailed
by the Lagos-based Nigerian Stock Exchange today.  
 Revenue declined to 62.7 billion naira compared with 63.8
billion naira, it said. The company proposed a dividend of 86
kobo per share.  
          
          


  


        